<div class="project-text">
    <h3>The Project</h3>
    <p>About four years of pure newsletter work. B2B, B2C, advertising, local, global, interviews, essays, guides, news. My old creative director and I always called the Nestle work "the newsletter gym", and that is exactly what it was.</p>
    <p>Here I learned ongoing client communication, not selling or chasing engagement, just the standard pipeline: order, delivery, maintenance. Alongside that came templating, automation and efficiency. I used what feels like every newsletter platform on the web. I learned informational copywriting rather than sales writing, deadlines, the way a format can stagnate and what it takes to refresh it without losing what makes it consistent. And above all, I learned that content matters more than the container.</p>
